A story about depth, love, and the decisions we make in pursuit of all things which require courage.

Trust in the process. What is meant for you cannot miss you. #angelitafilm

Directed and shot by: @Josiahwg 
Josi I am so spectacularly proud of you. Your vision brought all these people together and made this come to life.

Starring:  @ChelseaKauai  and  @samkolder. Sam to do this with you of all people and the way it came together. I’m sure everyone gets something different from it but to me this is the story of us.

This film would not have been possible without the incredible safety dive team of @tulum.breathtaking and @camitorresph. Filming at 100 ft most days meant they were figuring out logistics to keep us all safe. I trust you with my life and consider you friends for life.

Body and all around hype man: @sashajuliard

Edited by  @emmett_sparling 
Colorist  @JVKE 
Original Score "Angelita" by @matthewmorganmusic

Shot on Sony A7SIII + Nauticam Dive Housing. 
Custom fit wetsuits from @oceanerfreediving

We are so immensely grateful to you all for watching. Thank you 🙏🏼

Headphones recommended. “Nothing with a purpose is ever lost.” Directed + edited by @emmett_sparling 
Starring @chelseakauai @moore_rachel 
Full credits and backstory in Emmett’s caption.

Emmett started this script while in lockdown last year and from the moment he showed it to me I was enchanted with the story of the Voyager records.

Months later we finally were in the same location and filmed the dialogue during a sultry morning in French Polynesia. I still have a very hard time listening to myself on camera (thank you Emmett for your patience with my umms, likes, and other filler words.🙉) 

But truly there is nothing better than creating with friends.

This is an hommage to nature, to friendship, and to the human desire to leave a legacy.

What would you include if you were in charge of creating a record of life on earth?

node.text:
Why do you love the things you do? I used to ask myself this question a lot - why freediving, highlining, acroyoga, surfing?

Then I read a book on the science of flow state a few years ago and it made everything make more sense - all these activities fully immerse me in the now. That part of my mind that’s usually thinking about the past or worried about the future is traded for one of deep presence and focus.

I care about this research because it shows people who work to have flow in their lives are the happiest people on earth. Yet we are collectively spending less time doing these activities as society gets more busy, or more serious and our time and attention are distracted by endless forms of easy entertainment.

Where you find flow state is entirely up to you. Mine happens to be walking on a little rope between two trees or spinning around on someone’s feet. But it’s something I feel very passionate about everyone experiencing.

True flow state opens up a world where getting better is inherently fun. It is fulfillment that cannot be bought in fame or luxury or sugary distractions, but simply in honest effort, paid for with presence and is the intrinsic reward for reaching deeper into what we are capable of.

This film was made in partnership with @corona studios and in collaboration with @emmettsparling. Thank you so much to both of you for helping this come to life.

Additional footage provided by @samkolder and @kylormelton.

Headphones recommended.

@emmett_sparling x @chelseakauai

Emmett is SO talented and one of my best friends and favorite people to work with.

That being said we spent two weeks filming in French Polynesia in what felt like a very uninspired uphill battle. Nothing was clicking or falling into place and I was struggling emotionally with a lot of personal things.

Much of the middle part of the narrative came from that place of me really needing the ocean and all she teaches me.

Towards the end of the trip Emmett came to me with a paragraph in his notebook and was like “what do you think about this?”. It would end up becoming the opening lines and so Lady and the Sea was born.

In a wave of creativity we changed the concept of the film, I locked myself in my room and wrote the rest. We filmed the opening scene that evening and we finally felt like this was the story we wanted to tell.

We’re so excited to share this labor of love with you all.

To the places and people that grow us, hold space for us, and teach us how to live more fully. This is about you and for you. Thank you for the lessons.

node.text:
Water in the desert for the first time in a decade. Even these perfect early morning reflections only lasted a few minutes before a heavy wind storm came through. Either through research or lucky happenstance i love seeking out rare experiences that are hard to replicate.

Earlier this year heavy rains swept through the already stunning Soussouvlei sand dunes of Namibia and flooded these clay pans.

It happens about once every 10-15 years and I’m so so stoked we could make it there to see it before it evaporated soon after!
—-
A huge thank you to @jandre_namibia_photo_ for getting us to the right spots at the right time. If you’re looking for an incredible photography tour guide in Namibia this is your guy.

node.text:
Smiles for days when there’s warm weather + waves.☀️🏝 Shooting for @roxy. I actually didn’t grow up surfing. I started learning when I was 17, which felt suuper late being from Hawaii.

Years earlier, going through my very awkward teen phase, I remember having a poster of a Roxy girl ad on my wall and thinking how amazingly cool it was that this freckled local girl in the photo was traveling around - surfing! WHAT A DREAM.

It amazes how that single image still is imprinted in my head. And how, even now, with millions of images being put out daily we can so resonate with one that it makes us go - wow I want to try that or maybe I could do that.

And you can. Trust me I fully, totally, completely sucked when I started surfing (or taking photos or diving or anything I tried). I didn’t make it out past the whitewash the first time I surfed. I went back to the beach, coughed up a ton of water and slept for two hours.😂 But I kept that picture in my head and somehow stayed motivated.

It is not lost on me that 16 years later I’m the one in the ad now. I think daily about what kind of legacy I hope to leave with that young girl who used to be me. The little note I would want to press into her hand:

You are so capable of becoming what you’re inspired by.
-
Thank you @samkolder for helping capture these. Roxy’s new #OnTheBeach collection is out now!

Such an unexpectedly magical sunset, paired with the low tide reflections to make it even better. I missed these warm weather days and my never miss a sunset habit☺️🌅 I got a ton of questions about how I did this effect and it’s super easy. To use it:

-click on the ✨ symbol in your stories or reels
- swipe until you see one that says “watery” and has this 🌈 effect
- see what looks cool! In stories you can apply it afterwards too you don’t need to film with it. 

Tag me if you do, would love to see what you make! Or are there other cool ones you like to use? 🙃
